WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.500
<v Dr. Patel>Welcome back, everyone. Let's get straight into the data from this week's rollout.

00:00:06.500 --> 00:00:14.000
<v Maria>So we hit 23% adoption in the first 72 hours, which is well above what we forecasted. The team has been incredible.

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:18.500
<v Dr. Patel>Twenty three. And what was the forecast?

00:00:18.500 --> 00:00:22.000
<v Maria>Twelve to fifteen.

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:28.500
<v Dr. Patel>Maria, that's almost double. Why? Tell me you have a theory.

00:00:28.500 --> 00:00:38.000
<v Maria>I think the in-app tour did a lot of heavy lifting. We tested a version without it on five percent of accounts and adoption was flat. Tour is doing the work.

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:45.000
<v James>That tracks with what I'm seeing in support. Tickets are down forty percent week over week, even with way more active users.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:50.500
<v Dr. Patel>Down forty? While usage is up? James, are you sure?

00:00:50.500 --> 00:00:56.000
<v James>I pulled the numbers twice. It is genuinely down. People are figuring it out without us.

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:02.500
<v Dr. Patel>Okay, this is the first feature in two years where the data is better than the plan. So what's the catch?

00:01:02.500 --> 00:01:11.000
<v Maria>Honestly? The catch is that we don't know how durable it is. Three days is not a trend. We need another two weeks before I'd call this a win.

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:15.000
<v James>And the cost per session is up nine percent. We're going to feel that on the infra bill.

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:21.000
<v Dr. Patel>Nine percent. Worth it if adoption holds. Not worth it if it normalizes back to fifteen. James, can you model both?

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:24.000
<v James>By Friday.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
<v Dr. Patel>Good. Maria, beautiful work. Let's keep the champagne on ice.
